\begin_layout Standard
In conclusion, we presented a new system that profiles energy consumption
 pattern of individuals based on raw RSSI readings among active RFID tags
 and readers.
 Our detection scheme gives reasonably successful detection rate as in the
 table 
\begin_inset LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Token-Issue-Success,"

\end_inset

.
 While analyzing energy consumption pattern of users, we found the system
 can profile two interesting aspects of energy profiles: first, total energy
 consumption, which gives us how much energy is consumed by an individual
 whether it's useful or not, and second, total wasted energy, which implies
 the energy wasted by an individual unintentionally.
 By notifying the total amount of energy users consume, on one hand, the
 system can encourage users to reduce their energy consumption.
 If users are aware of their consumption and their need for energy on the
 regular basis, users could plan and optimize theirs.
 On the other hand, the system also gives users the information when they
 unintentionally wasted energy.
 In addition to that, users also could optimize their energy consumption
 schedule by observing their energy usage pattern on a daily basis.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the future works, we can further the detection algorithm by correlating
 multiple RSSI readings among appliances.
 Along with that, more complex deployment setting among collocated appliances
 and more users can reveal more interesting observations regarding energy
 optimizing concerns.
 For the system to be more useful, the system will have more user-friendly
 interfaces.
 
